---
spec: openexam/1
title: MAC-address regex
points: 2
addons:
  - regex
tags:
  - code
---

Write a regex that matches a colon-separated MAC address — six hexadecimal pairs joined by single colons. Examples that should match: `00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E`, `de:ad:be:ef:00:01`. Case-insensitive.

::: regex { pattern="[0-9a-fA-F]{2}(:[0-9a-fA-F]{2}){5}", placeholder="e.g. 00:1A:2B:3C:4D:5E" }
:::
